. Dawn (25 May 1884 – 2 February 1975) was an early American film director. He made several improvements on the matte shot to apply it to motion picture, and was the first director to use rear projection in film production.\n\n", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T12:36:23.967887+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2792, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norman_Dawn"}], "uuid": "8e43ee80-150f-4ee1-96bd-6dd9950a209d", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "25882", "external_references": [{"id": 11894, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q3343763"}, {"id": 11895, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "76578157"}, {"id": 11896, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no91015707"}, {"id": 11897, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no91015707"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-13T12:31:39.497151+10:00"}, {"id": 22244, "name": "Charles MacMahon", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2043282, "title": "For the term of his natural life", "work_id": 79851, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1861-01-01", "date_of_death": "1917-01-01", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "The MacMahon brothers were entrepreneurs in Australian show business. Chief among them were James MacMahon (1856 or c. 1858 – 29 April 1915) and Charles MacMahon  (1861 – 27 June 1917), who together and separately toured a large number of stage shows.\nTheir younger brothers, Joseph (died November 1918) and William (died August 1923), were involved in many of those activities.\nIn later years James acquired the nickname \"Mighty Atom\", perhaps a reference to Marie Corelli's novel. and Charles had some success as a filmmaker.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-0